{
  "texts": [
    "We compare the pretrained model with a From Scratch variant that shares the same architecture but is trained only on warmup data.Few-shot warmup and the importance of pretraining.",
    "Table 1 summarizes the effect of 5-video and 15-video warmups.",
    "With five target-robot videos, the pretrained model achieves an overall success rate of 80%, whereas the scratch model attains 25%.",
    "Increasing warmup to fifteen videos yields limited additional improvement for the pretrained model (82.5%) and marginal change for the scratch variant (30%).",
    "These results indicate that the majority of TraceGen's performance stems from pretraining, with warmup primarily aligning pretrained motion priors with task-specific configurations."
  ]
}